  "Question": "<p>A bug starts at time <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_832\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mn>0</mn> </math></span> at position <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_833\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mn>0</mn> </math></span>. At each step, the bug either moves to the right by <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_834\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mn>1</mn> </math></span> step <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_835\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"(+1)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </math></span> with probability <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_836\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"1/2\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>/</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, or returns to the origin with probability <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_837\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"1/2\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>/</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </math></span>. What is the expected number of steps for this bug to reach position <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_838\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"N\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>N</mi> </math></span>?</p> <p>I tried to first find the possibility that this bug reaches <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_839\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"N\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>N</mi> </math></span> as the number of steps goes to infinity. The recurrence equation I find is <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_840\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"p_{n}=\\frac{1}{2}p_{n-1}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>p</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msub> <mi>p</mi> <mrow> <mi>n</mi> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msub> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>, where <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_841\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"p_{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msub> <mi>p</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msub> </math></span> is the possibility for the bug starting at position <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_842\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"n\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>n</mi> </math></span> to reach <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_843\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"N\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>N</mi> </math></span>. We also have the boundary condition <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_844\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"p_{N}=1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>p</mi> <mi>N</mi> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span>. Then we see that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_845\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"p_{N-1}=2\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>p</mi> <mrow> <mi>N</mi> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, and that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_846\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"p_{0}=2^{N}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>p</mi> <mn>0</mn> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <msup> <mn>2</mn> <mi>N</mi> </msup> </mrow> </math></span>, which doesn't make sense at all because it is greater than <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_847\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mn>1</mn> </math></span>. I think I should sort out the value of probability first, and think about the number of expected steps later.</p> <p>I'm sure there is something wrong with the recurrence equation, but what's wrong about it?</p>",
